        </button>
        <button
          onClick={scrollRight}
          className="w-12 h-12 bg-white rounded-full shadow-lg flex items-center justify-center hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors"
        >
          <svg className="w-5 h-5 text-gray-700" />
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    {/* Scrollable Container */}
    <div 
      ref={scrollContainerRef}
      className="flex gap-6 overflow-x-auto scrollbar-hide scroll-smooth snap-x snap-mandatory pb-4"
    >
      {similarDesigns.map((similar) => (
        <Link
          key={similar.id}
          href={`/inspo/${similar.categorySlug}/${similar.id}`}
          className="flex-shrink-0 w-80 snap-start group"
        >
          <div className="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-300 overflow-hidden">
            <div className="relative aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden">
              <img 
                src={similar.imageUrl}
                alt={similar.altText}
                className="w-full h-full object-cover transform group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-500"
              />
              
              {/* Quick Stats Overlay */}
              <div className="absolute bottom-0 inset-x-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/80 to-transparent p-4">
                <div className="flex items-center gap-4 text-white text-sm">
                  <span className="flex items-center gap-1">
                    <svg className="w-4 h-4" /> {similar.likes}
                  </span>
                  <span className="flex items-center gap-1">
                    <svg className="w-4 h-4" /> {similar.saves}
                  </span>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              {/* Heart Button */}
              <button
                onClick={(e) => {
                  e.preventDefault();
                  handleQuickLike(similar.id);
                }}
                className="absolute top-3 right-3 w-10 h-10 bg-white/90 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center hover:bg-white transition-colors"
              >
                <svg className="w-5 h-5 text-burgundy-600" />
              </button>
            </div>
            
            <div className="p-4">
              <h3 className="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 line-clamp-2 group-hover:text-burgundy-600 transition-colors">
                {similar.title}
              </h3>
              
              <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                {similar.tags.slice(0, 2).map((tag) => (
                  <span 
                    key={tag}
                    className="px-2 py-1 bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 rounded-full text-xs font-medium"
                  >
                    {tag}
                  </span>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </Link>
      ))}
    </div>
    
    {/* Mobile: Show scroll indicators */}
    <div className="md:hidden flex justify-center gap-2 mt-6">
      {Array.from({ length: Math.ceil(similarDesigns.length / 2) }).map((_, i) => (
        <button
          key={i}
          onClick={() => scrollToSlide(i)}
          className={`w-2 h-2 rounded-full transition-all ${
            currentSlide === i ? 'w-8 bg-burgundy-600' : 'bg-gray-300'
          }`}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
```

---

## üéØ **CONTENT PLACEMENT STRATEGY (800+ WORDS SEO)**

### **Distribution Across Page Sections:**

**Main Inspo Hub Page (/inspo):**
- Hero section: 50-75 words (headline + subheadline)
- About Inspo collapsible: 250-300 words
- FAQ section: 400-450 words (8-10 questions √ó 50 words each)
- Category descriptions: 30-50 words each √ó 8 categories = 240-400 words
- **Total: ~940-1,225 words**

**Category Pages (/inspo/[category]):**
- Hero section: 30-50 words (description)
- About This Style collapsible: 200-250 words
- Design Tips section: 150-200 words (3 tips √ó 50-70 words)
- FAQ section: 300-400 words (8-10 questions √ó 40-50 words)
- Related categories descriptions: 100-150 words
- Shop CTA section: 50-75 words
- Image alt texts: 50-100 words (across all gallery images)
- **Total: ~880-1,225 words**

**Individual Design Pages (/inspo/[category]/[designId]):**
- Design description: 75-100 words
- Design breakdown sections: 200-250 words
- Products descriptions: 150-200 words
- Similar designs section: 50-75 words
- Meta descriptions & schema: 100-150 words
- **Total: ~575-775 words** (lighter, more visual focus)

### **SEO Content Visibility Strategy:**

**Immediately Visible (10% of content):**
- Hero headlines & descriptions
- Category cards descriptions
- Design titles & tags
- Stats & badges

**Progressive Disclosure (40% of content):**
- Collapsible "About" sections (click to expand)
- FAQ accordions (expand on demand)
- Design Tips cards (visible but concise)

**Hidden but Crawlable (50% of content):**
- Image alt texts (invisible to users, visible to crawlers)
- Schema markup descriptions
- Meta descriptions
- OpenGraph descriptions
- Breadcrumb titles

**Result:** Users see 90% visuals, 10% text. Crawlers see 800+ words of relevant content.

---

## üîß **IMPLEMENTATION PHASES**

### **PRE-PHASE: Deep Competitive Research (MANDATORY)**

Before any coding, agent MUST complete comprehensive analysis:

**1. SERP Analysis (Primary Keywords):**

Research top 10 ranking pages for each category keyword:
```
Primary Keywords to Analyze:
- "nail design inspiration"
- "french tip nail ideas"
- "ombre nail designs"
- "chrome nail art"
- [each category's primary keyword]
```

**For Each Competitor, Extract:**
- Exact URL and domain authority
- Word count on page
- Number of images in gallery
- Gallery layout type (grid/masonry/slider)
- Filter options available
- SEO content placement strategy
- Schema types implemented (view source)
- Page load speed (GTmetrix/PageSpeed)
- Unique features/interactions
- Strengths (what they do well)
- Weaknesses/gaps (what they miss)

**Analyze SERP Features:**
- Featured Snippets present?
- People Also Ask questions
- Image pack results
- Video carousel
- Related searches
- Knowledge panel

**Calculate Competitive Benchmarks:**
```
Average word count across top 10: [X words]
Average images per page: [X images]
Common filter options: [list]
Most common schema types: [list]
Average page speed: [X seconds]
SERP features being won: [list]
```

**Identify Opportunities:**
- Content gaps none of top 10 address
- Poor user experience patterns
- Missing filter/sort options
- Slow load times to beat
- Schema opportunities (types not being used)
- SERP features not being won
- Better design/interaction opportunities

**2. Design Psychology Research:**

Analyze 5-10 top visual gallery sites:
```
Sites to Study:
- Pinterest.com (masonry layout king)
- Behance.net (portfolio galleries)
- Dribbble.com (design showcase)
- Unsplash.com (photo galleries)
- Awwwards.com (award-winning galleries)
```

**Extract Design Patterns:**
- Hover effect styles
- Like/save interaction patterns
- Filter UI patterns
- Loading animations
- Empty state designs
- Mobile gesture support

**3. Schema Research:**

Research schema implementation on top competitors:
- Which schema types are they using?
- How are they structuring ImageObject?
- Are they using CollectionPage?
- FAQ schema patterns
- Missed schema opportunities

**4. Keyword Research Deep Dive:**

For EACH category, extract:

**Primary Keyword:**
- Search volume
- Keyword difficulty
- Search intent (informational/commercial)
- Current ranking pages

**Cluster Keywords (5-10 per category):**
- Related design style terms
- Color variations
- Technique names
- Seasonal variations
- Example: "french tips" ‚Üí "colored french tips", "reverse french", "french ombre", "french with glitter"

**Long-Tail Keywords (10-15 per category):**
- Question-based queries
- "how to" queries
- "best for" queries
- Comparison queries
- Example: "how to do french tips at home", "best nail shape for french tips", "french tips vs full color"

**Voice Search Queries (10+ per category):**
- Natural language questions
- Conversational phrases
- "What are..." queries
- "How do I..." queries
- Example: "What nail polish colors work for french tips?", "How do I make french tips last longer?"

**5. Present Research to User (BEFORE Phase 1):**

Agent delivers comprehensive report (<800 words, bullet format):
```
üîç INSPO SECTION COMPETITIVE ANALYSIS

PRIMARY KEYWORD: [keyword]
Search Volume: [X] | Difficulty: [X/100] | Intent: [informational]

TOP 10 COMPETITORS ANALYSIS:
1. [Domain] - [DA score]
   - Word count: [X words]
   - Images: [X gallery items]
   - Layout: [grid/masonry/slider]
   - Filters: [color, style, length available]
   - Strengths: [what they do well]
   - Weaknesses: [what they miss]
   - Schema: [types used]
   - Page speed: [X seconds]

2. [Domain] - [DA score]
   [repeat above metrics]

[...continue for top 10]

KEY METRICS SUMMARY:
- Avg word count: [X] ‚Üí OUR TARGET: [+15-25%] = [X words]
- Avg images: [X] ‚Üí OUR TARGET: [+20%] = [X images]
- Common filters: [color, style, length, occasion]
- Missing filters: [difficulty, season, nail shape] ‚Üê OPPORTUNITY
- Avg page speed: [X]s ‚Üí OUR TARGET: <2s
- Schema usage: 40% use ImageGallery, 60% skip CollectionPage ‚Üê OPPORTUNITY

SERP FEATURES PRESENT:
‚úÖ Image Pack (position 2)
‚úÖ People Also Ask (8 questions)
‚ùå Featured Snippet (OPPORTUNITY)
‚ùå Video Carousel (not applicable)

PEOPLE ALSO ASK QUESTIONS (Target for FAQ):
1. "What are the most popular nail designs?"
2. "How do I choose nail designs for my skin tone?"
3. "What nail shape is trending?"
[...list all PAA questions]

CONTENT GAPS TO EXPLOIT:
‚Üí No competitor offers difficulty filters
‚Üí None provide estimated time per design
‚Üí Missing product recommendations integrated with designs
‚Üí No "design breakdown" feature (colors, techniques)
‚Üí Poor mobile filter UX across all competitors
‚Üí Only 2/10 have quality FAQ sections

DESIGN OPPORTUNITIES:
‚Üí Better hover effects (competitors use basic overlays)
‚Üí Like/save functionality (only 3/10 have this)
‚Üí Smoother masonry layout (many use janky JS libraries)
‚Üí Better filter chip design (most are boring buttons)
‚Üí Empty state designs (most show nothing)

SCHEMA OPPORTUNITIES:
‚Üí Use CollectionPage (only 40% use this)
‚Üí Implement ImageGallery with associatedMedia
‚Üí Add FAQPage schema (only 30% have this)
‚Üí ItemList for gallery items
‚Üí Comprehensive breadcrumbs

YOUR WINNING STRATEGY:
‚Üí Target: 1,000-1,200 words per category page (vs avg 850)
‚Üí Target: 50+ images per category (vs avg 40)
‚Üí Implement 5 filter types (vs avg 3)
‚Üí Page speed: <2s LCP (vs avg 3.5s)
‚Üí Win Featured Snippet with comparison table
‚Üí Win Image Pack with optimized alt texts
‚Üí Target 10 PAA questions in FAQ
‚Üí Unique: Design breakdown feature
‚Üí Unique: Difficulty + time filters
‚Üí Unique: Integrated product recommendations

KEYWORD STRATEGY:
Primary: [keyword]
Clusters: [list 5-10]
Long-tail: [list 10-15]
Voice queries: [list 10+]
Semantic: [list 15-20]

NEXT STEPS:
‚úÖ User reviews & approves strategy
‚úÖ Proceed to Phase 1: File preparation
```

**User MUST review and approve before proceeding to Phase 1.**

